3070 N Oakland Ave #4

PPi,

I came across your company on <http://JobsInMadison.com|JobsInMadison.com> and became interested in your Software Engineering position. After looking more into your company, I became intrigued by your long-term care tools so I have decided to apply.

Since 2014 I have been working in the technology industry where I have been repeatedly recognized for my hard work and ability to exceed expectations. Currently, I am responsible for full lifecycle development of VB .NET web scraping software from initial requirement gathering from our customers to coding, testing, documentation and implementation. I also am also serving as a mentor for new interns where I provide guidance while they learn new technologies.

I have skills using VB .NET, TFS, ASP .NET, Microsoft Azure, and SQL - all of which were mentioned in the job posting. My ability to quickly learn has me exploring new programming languages frequently so I am sure to keep up with the latest technologies. I also have experience working with Agile development methodologies from school, work, and my own personal side projects. My personal side projects include web development, console utilities, iOS applications(Swift), and much much more. 

My leadership experience along with my entrepreneurial and creative personality would fit in with CenterX’s drive to provide the best e-prescribing tools available. If you think that I would make a good fit for CenterX, please contact me at <mailto:andrew@budziszek.com|andrew@budziszek.com> or by phone at <tel:(262)617-6215|(262)617-6215>. I look forward to speaking with you!

Thank you for your consideration,

Andrew Budziszek
